                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "p",
                "elements": [
                  {
                    "type": "r",
                    "text": "1. Understand current risk: Identify the systems, accounts, and data that support daily operations."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "p",
                "elements": [
                  {
                    "type": "r",
                    "text": "2. Protect important assets: Use safeguards such as MFA, backups, software updates, and role-based access."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "p",
                "elements": [
                  {
                    "type": "r",
                    "text": "3. Prepare to respond: Define who should act when an incident is detected and how the business will recover."
                  }
                ]
              },
